                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">first half of the fourteenth century script?</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>

                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12412Maksimos">Māksimos</persName>
                        <date notBefore="1300" notAfter="1350">First half of the 14th cent. </date>
                        <desc>The hand might be characterised through straight downstrokes, rectangular
                  ‘feet’ without any decoration, the scribe might have been trained to write
                  during the first half of the fourteenth century, since there is clear tendency
                  to the ancient way of writing. </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">used to lay out initial pages, punctuation, numerals and
                  names</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">14th-15th cent.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>

                        <desc>downstrokes are slightly bent, feet with hairlines, directed to the
                  right</desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">used to lay out initial pages, punctuation, numerals and
                  names</seg>
                     </handNote>
